                        <note>Text revised after Mommsen and Korhonen, using new photographs</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#WS">
                <p>Marcia Marylla lived 5- years. Markia Marulla lived 5- years.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Provenance is uncertain, but likely Catania (for another such bilingual compare IMusCat 74 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic0348">ISicily0348</ref>. The Greek text is now almost wholly lost, partially reported by Mommsen in <ref target="http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/650761">CIL 10.7078</ref>. Mommsen was unable to read the name on line 3 in full, but the traces printed in CIL appear compatible with the name in line 1. The surviving traces of line 3 on the left-hand fragment are clearly compatible with Α ΕΖ (the epsilon being lunate).</p>
            </div>
